definition.value: An aminopyrimidine having the amino group at the 4-position together with methyl and phosphooxymethyl groups at the 2- and 5-positions respectively.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resuting from removal of a proton from both carboxy groups of 4-fumarylacetoacetic acid.

A glyceride that is glycerol in which any two of the hydroxy groups have been acylated. In the structure shown, two of the R groups (positions not specified) are acyl groups while the remaining R group can be either H or an alkyl group.
